<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-31T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-31T01:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1402: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-31T14:00:00+08:00">January 31, 1932—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 31—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>161. Following from American Consul General at Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“January 30, 4 p.m. My January 24, 5 p.m. Commander of destroyer
                                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SSJH1"><hi rend="italic">Simpson</hi></persName> has asked me for views
                                    regarding additional vessels for Nanking. I have suggested 1
                                    destroyer be stationed at Wuhu where 50 Americans reside with
                                    others in the interior and 1 additional ship at Nanking where
                                    resident Americans number approximately 180. Original number of
                                    vessels requested has been reduced since only 4 additional are
                                    available for entire Yangtze.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>